Optional, NOT shipped or depended upon — editable Word (OMML) export
--------------------------------------------------------------------
Formulyze does not bundle or depend on any copyleft software. Editable Word
(.docx) equation export is OFF by default: the library ships no MathML→OMML
converter. To enable it, install a converter yourself and inject it:

    import { mml2omml } from 'mathml2omml';         // LGPL-3.0-or-later
    import { setOmmlConverter } from 'formulyze';
    setOmmlConverter({ toOmml: (mathml) => mml2omml(mathml) });

`mathml2omml` is LGPL-3.0. Because Formulyze neither ships nor depends on it,
the package remains MIT; the LGPL obligations apply only if you choose to add
that library to your own project. Without a converter, Word export degrades
gracefully to a valid .docx containing the formula as text.
